  <title>Organize your apps</title>

  <p>Add folders to the desktop</p>

  <comment>{video 2}</comment>

  <steps>
    <item>
      <p>To add a new Folder, right-click the desktop and select <gui>Add
      folder</gui>.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Pick an icon for your new Folder.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Type a name for your new Folder ("School" for example) and hit
      Enter.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>You have added a new folder to the desktop. Great! Now click on the
      close button on the top-right of the window to go back to the desktop.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Drag and drop the icons you want into your folder.</p>
    </item>
  </steps>
